verbose_text: Hypoxic factors are targeted in cancer therapy to use hypoxia mediated cell death to kill cancerous cells; therefore, it is important to take into consideration that while pro angiogenic factors, such as VEGF will be down-regulated, this treatment may either up- or down-regulate IL-1alpha, depending on the cell type.
